.5. Aliases

.5.1. What are aliases?

an alias allows a string to be substituted for a word when it is used as the first word of a simple command.
the shell maintais a list of alias that can be modified with the "alias" command, running it with no options dispplays the list of aliases

for permanent use you may change the init files of your shell

